article.headline: Liberty 60, Radford 55
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- Evan Gordon and Jesse Sanders scored 16 points each as Liberty knocked off Radford 60-55 on Saturday. The Flames (10-11, 5-4 Big South Conference) took a lead with 9:29 left in the game and didn't relinquish it to snap a two-game skid, despite 26 points and 15 rebounds from Radford's Art Parakhouski. Liberty took a 42-41 lead on Chris Perez's layup and increased it to 47-41 on Gordon's layup with 7:04 to play. Radford (10-8, 6-3) cut the lead to 49-47 on Blake Smith's jumper with 4:12 left, but Carter McMasters dunked to push the lead to 51-47 with 3:31 to play. The Highlanders cut the lead to 58-55 on Parakhouski's three-point play with 21 seconds remaining, but Jeremy Anderson hit two free throws for a 60-55 advantage with 15 seconds left. Radford shot 36 percent in the second half (9-for-25) and was 1-for-22 from the 3-point line (4.5 percent).
